contents: Impaired social interaction   (9) <u>is most easily the identifiable symptom</u> of ASD. An infant with ASD may not respond to or interact with people or may focus exclusively on one object. Some children with ASD begin to develop normally and then withdraw from social interactions. Children may not respond to their names or may avoid eye contact. Individuals with ASD often can’t understand tone of voice, expressions, or other cues. (10) ___________.
